article.headline: Kent St. 60, Ball St. 54
article.story: MUNCIE, Ind. (AP) -- Armon Gates came off the bench to score 21 points to lead Kent State to a 60-54 victory over Ball State on Wednesday. Gates shot 6-of-11 from the floor and 5-of-10 from behind the arc for the Golden Flashes (11-8, 4-2 Mid-American Conference). Mike Scott added nine points and eight rebounds for Kent State. Skip Mills and Micah Rollin each scored 14 points to lead the Cardinals (6-13, 2-4), who suffered their seventh loss of the last nine games. A 3-pointer by Gates gave Kent State a 16-6 lead to open the game and the Golden Flashes led 36-26 at halftime. Ball State used a 13-4 run over the first 4:59 of the second half to pull to within one point, but the Cardinals committed nine fouls over the final 14:27 which Kent State turned into nine points at the free throw line.
